          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Fair Medical Debt Reporting Act </b></p> <p>This bill prohibits credit reporting agencies from including certain medical debt on a consumer report. Specifically, agencies may not include on a report medical debt that has not been placed for collection, medical debt that was placed for collection within a year prior to the report, or medical debt fully paid or settled within a certain period of time. </p> <p>Before a person provides information regarding a consumer's medical debt to a credit reporting agency, that person must notify the consumer of the restrictions regarding the reporting of medical debt and provide the consumer with details regarding the medical debt. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-10-06T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
